---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import Navbar from "../components/Navbar.astro";
import Footer from "../components/Footer.astro";
---

<Layout title="About the Seerah Series | Authenticity & Mission">
    <Navbar />

    <header class="page-header">
        <div class="container text-center">
            <h1>
                The Mission of <span class="gradient-text">Seerah Podcast</span>
            </h1>
            <p>
                Bringing the timeless story of Prophet Muhammad ﷺ to the modern
                generation.
            </p>
        </div>
    </header>

    <main class="container about-container">
        <div class="about-grid">
            <div class="about-text animate-fade-in">
                <h2>Shaykh Abdul Nasir Jangda</h2>
                <p>
                    The <strong
                        >Seerah - Life of the Prophet (sallallahu alayhi
                        wasallam)</strong
                    > podcast is authored and presented by <strong
                        >Shaykh Abdul Nasir Jangda</strong
                    > of the <a
                        href="https://www.qalam.institute"
                        target="_blank"
                        class="accent-link">Qalam Institute</a
                    >.
                </p>
                <p>
                    This series, often referred to as <em>"Seerah Pearls"</em>,
                    aims to highlight tantalizing learning points from each
                    stage of the Prophet's ﷺ life. It goes beyond dry facts to
                    provide eternal practical lessons for everyday life.
                </p>

                <div class="definition-box glass-card">
                    <h3>What is 'Seerah'?</h3>
                    <p>
                        Linguistically, it means 'a path' or 'to walk in a
                        particular direction'. More figuratively, it refers to
                        the Prophetic biography—covering everything from his
                        daily practices and physical characteristics to his
                        family life and expeditions.
                    </p>
                </div>

                <div class="values-grid">
                    <div class="value-item">
                        <h3>Authentic Sources</h3>
                        <p>
                            Cross-referenced with classical works like Ibn Ishaq
                            and Ibn Hisham.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="value-item">
                        <h3>Humanizing History</h3>
                        <p>
                            Aiming to engender true love for the Prophet ﷺ
                            through knowing his character.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="about-image animate-fade-in">
                <div class="glass-card">
                    <img
                        src="thumb.jpg"
                        alt="Seerah Podcast Author - Shaykh Abdul Nasir Jangda"
                    />
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <section class="mission-highlight animate-fade-in">
            <div class="mission-grid">
                <div class="mission-content glass-card">
                    <h2>The Quranic Pattern</h2>
                    <p>
                        The Quran itself states that there is not a better
                        example than the Prophet Muhammad (sallallahu alayhi
                        wasallam) himself:
                    </p>

                    <blockquote class="book-quote">
                        <p>
                            "There has certainly been for you in the Messenger
                            of Allah an excellent pattern for anyone whose hope
                            is in Allah and the Last Day and [who] remembers
                            Allah often."
                        </p>
                        <cite>— Quran 33:21</cite>
                    </blockquote>

                    <p>
                        This series aims to humanise the Prophet Muhammad
                        (sallallahu alayhi wasallam) and provide eternal
                        practical lessons, as well as engender love for the best
                        of humankind.
                    </p>

                    <p class="impact-text">
                        How can you possibly love someone you do not know?
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>
    </main>

    <Footer />
</Layout>

<style>
    .page-header {
        padding: 6rem 0 4rem;
        text-align: center;
    }

    h1 {
        font-size: clamp(2.2rem, 8vw, 3.5rem);
        margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    }
    .page-header p {
        font-size: clamp(1.1rem, 4vw, 1.25rem);
        color: var(--text-muted);
        max-width: 700px;
        margin: 0 auto;
    }

    .about-container {
        margin-bottom: 8rem;
    }

    .about-grid {
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: 1.2fr 1fr;
        gap: 4rem;
        align-items: center;
    }

    .about-text h2 {
        font-size: clamp(1.75rem, 6vw, 2.5rem);
        margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    }
    .about-text p {
        font-size: clamp(1.05rem, 3.5vw, 1.15rem);
        color: var(--text-muted);
        margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
        line-height: 1.7;
    }

    .definition-box {
        padding: 1.5rem;
        margin: 2rem 0;
        border-left: 4px solid var(--cerulean);
        background: rgba(72, 119, 146, 0.05);
    }

    .definition-box h3 {
        font-size: 1.25rem;
        margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
        color: var(--oxford-navy);
    }

    .accent-link {
        color: var(--cerulean);
        font-weight: 600;
        text-decoration: underline;
    }

    .values-grid {
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
        gap: 2rem;
        margin-top: 3rem;
    }

    .value-item h3 {
        font-size: 1.3rem;
        margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
        color: var(--cerulean);
    }

    .about-image .glass-card {
        padding: 1rem;
    }
    .about-image img {
        border-radius: var(--radius-md);
    }

    /* Mission Section Styles */
    .mission-highlight {
        margin-top: 6rem;
    }

    .mission-content {
        padding: 4rem;
        text-align: center;
        background: linear-gradient(
            135deg,
            var(--white) 0%,
            var(--platinum) 100%
        );
    }

    .mission-content h2 {
        font-size: clamp(1.75rem, 6vw, 2.5rem);
        margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    }

    .mission-content p {
        font-size: 1.2rem;
        color: var(--text-muted);
        max-width: 800px;
        margin: 0 auto 1.5rem;
    }

    .book-quote {
        margin: 3rem auto;
        max-width: 700px;
        padding: 2.5rem;
        background: var(--oxford-navy);
        color: white;
        border-radius: var(--radius-md);
        position: relative;
    }

    .book-quote p {
        font-size: clamp(1.1rem, 4.5vw, 1.5rem);
        font-style: italic;
        color: white;
        line-height: 1.5;
        margin-bottom: 1rem;
    }

    .book-quote cite {
        display: block;
        text-align: right;
        font-weight: 600;
        color: #e7a53f;
    }

    .impact-text {
        font-size: clamp(1.4rem, 5vw, 1.8rem) !important;
        font-weight: 700;
        color: var(--oxford-navy) !important;
        margin-top: 3rem !important;
    }

    @media (max-width: 1024px) {
        .about-grid {
            grid-template-columns: 1fr;
            text-align: center;
        }

        .values-grid {
            grid-template-columns: 1fr;
        }

        .mission-content {
            padding: 2.5rem 1.5rem;
        }

        .book-quote {
            padding: 1.5rem;
        }
    }

    @media (max-width: 768px) {
        .page-header {
            padding: 4rem 0 3rem;
        }
    }
</style>
